This paper deals with the problem of dense video captioning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end transformer model, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of self-attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in deep learning and could place the paper in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also evaluates its model on two datasets, ActivityNet Captions and YouCookII, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to generating captions, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
